Task 3.1: Network Concepts

1. OSI Model

7 Layers of OSI Model:
Physical Layer
Data Link Layer
Network Layer
Transport Layer
Session Layer
Presentation Layer
Application Layer


Example Protocols for Each Layer:
Layer	        Protocol Example
Physical	Ethernet (cables, signals)
Data Link	MAC, ARP
Network	        IP (Internet Protocol)
Transport	TCP, UDP
Session	        NetBIOS
Presentation	SSL/TLS
Application	HTTP, FTP, DNS


Which Layer TCP Operates At?
TCP operates at the Transport Layer (Layer 4)
Provides reliable communication
Handles error checking and data delivery


2. IP Addressing

Difference Between Public and Private IP
Public IP	                Private IP
Accessible over internet	Used inside local network
Unique globally	                Reused in different networks
Assigned by ISP	                Assigned by router


Private IP Ranges
Class	  Range
Class A	  10.0.0.0 – 10.255.255.255
Class B	  172.16.0.0 – 172.31.255.255
Class C	  192.168.0.0 – 192.168.255.255


Is 192.168.1.100 Public or Private?
It is a Private IP Address

3. Protocols

Match Ports to Services

Port	Service
22	SSH
80	HTTP
443	HTTPS
3306	MySQL


Difference Between TCP and UDP
TCP	                        UDP
Connection-oriented	        Connectionless
Reliable (guarantees delivery)	Faster but unreliable
Error checking	                No guarantee of delivery
Used in HTTP, FTP	        Used in DNS, streaming


What is NAT?
NAT (Network Address Translation) converts private IP addresses into a public IP.
Why NAT is Needed:
Saves public IP addresses
Adds security (internal IP hidden)
Allows multiple devices to share one internet connection



